4. The program calls the function `fn1` with the argument `5` and assigns the returned value to the bit field `ad.o` of the structure.

5. The program declares a variable `ae` of type `signed`.

6. The program assigns the value of the bit field `ad.o` to the variable `ae`.

8. The program calculates the value of `t % (5 / ae)` and assigns it to the variable `r`.

9. The program has the expression `ad.o`, which does not have any effect.
